title: Saucon Valley's Kiele Riefenstahl, Northwestern girls dominate CL cross country championship
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Colonial League girls cross country championship -- Rapid Recap 
Saucon Valley freshman Kiele Riefenstahl took the first step towards being a four-time individual Colonial League champion when she won Wednesday afternoon’s individual race at DeSales University in 19 minutes and 46 seconds, 27 seconds ahead of runner-up Molly Tarvin of Northwestern Lehigh . 
The Tigers won their fifth consecutive team title, putting four runners in the top nine and scoring 36 points to second-place Wilson’s 74. 
Turning point: Wilson put three runners – Sydney Brannon , Abby Rustay and Gaby Vega (fourth, fifth and sixth) – in after Northwestern’s first two, but the Tigers had six finishers ahead of the next Warrior. 
Top performer: Riefenstahl was more or less in her own race the last half or it. She was dominant. 
What it means: Northwestern looks ready to battle Central Catholic at the District 11 Class AA meet. Riefenstahl, meanwhile, looks like she could be the next great Saucon Valley track/cross country runner after Alyssa Lombardo and Elizabeth Chikotas.
